# Asset Management

## Summary

Defines asset organization, image optimization, and manifest guidelines. Organizes assets in the public directory with proper naming conventions. References [i18n](mdc:.cursor/rules/i18n.mdc) for translation file organization and [styling](mdc:.cursor/rules/styling.mdc) for image component patterns.

## Directory structure

- Organize assets in public directory:
  - images/ for general images
  - locales/ for translation files
  - icons/ for site icons
- Use proper naming conventions:
  - Lowercase with hyphens
  - Include dimensions in filename when relevant
  - Use descriptive names

## Image optimization

- Provide multiple formats:
  - WebP as primary format
  - PNG/JPG as fallback
  - SVG for icons and simple graphics
- Follow optimization guidelines:
  - Compress all images
  - Use proper dimensions
  - Maintain aspect ratios
- Favicon requirements:
  - favicon-16x16.png
  - favicon-32x32.png
  - apple-touch-icon.png
  - android-chrome variants

## Example image component

```tsx
import Image from "next/image";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

interface OptimizedImageProps {
  src: string;
  alt: string;
  className?: string;
  priority?: boolean;
}

export const OptimizedImage = ({
  src,
  alt,
  className,
  priority = false,
}: OptimizedImageProps) => (
  <Image
    src={src}
    alt={alt}
    className={cn("object-cover", className)}
    priority={priority}
    quality={90}
    sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1200px) 50vw, 33vw"
  />
);
```

## Manifest guidelines

- Maintain proper manifest.json:
  - Include all required icons
  - Proper theme colors
  - Correct display modes
- Keep robots.txt updated:
  - Proper crawling rules
  - Sitemap reference
  - User-agent specifications
